               <msContents>
                  <summary>Loan of 30 talents, 3,000 drachmas. The borrower, Aurelius Didymos,  comes from the village of Pakerke, the lender from Oxyrhynchos.</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">Written along the fibers; on the verso, a 1-line docket</note>
                     <note type="general">26 lines; broken at right; other margins are preserved</note>
                     <note type="general">The ink in the subscription is rather faded</note>
                     <note type="general">Two hands are at work; the first that writes the main body is a large hand with few ligatures; the second for the subscription uses a lighter ink and is faster, smaller, and inclined to the right; the first hand probably writes the docket in the back</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">In Greek</textLang>
